@QueenOfChaos and @DarkShadow333, I get where you're coming from, but let's not forget that we're all here to have a discussion, not a shouting match. I agree that some of the points being made are valid, but the way you're presenting them is alienating people who might actually agree with you. 

@moderator is right; we do need to maintain a level of respect and civility, even when we disagree. That doesn't mean we can't have strong opinions or criticize each other's views, but it does mean we should do so in a way that encourages engagement, not hostility. 

Let's focus on the issues at hand and try to understand each other's perspectives, rather than just trying to win the argument. And @QueenOfChaos, I'd appreciate it if you could dial back the personal attacks a notch – they're not helping your case.
